commit.message:
Add support for Python 3.6-3.7, drop support for 2.6 and 3.4 (#44)

* Drop support for EOL Python 2.6 and 3.4

* Add python_requires to help pip

* Add support for Python 3.6 and 3.7

* Test on Python 3.8 beta

use html.escape instead of cgi.escape for python3 (#40)

Based on the following:

DeprecationWarning: cgi.escape is deprecated, use html.escape instead

added thead and tbody tags (#30)

* added thead and tbody tags

* updated README

XSS Attack Prevention by default (#28)

* escaping of text nodes to prevent XSS

* small beauty fix, use tuples for text types

* added a test for xss - fails because we passed a non-json string. let's fix this first

* added additional tests, catched a json.loads exception where the user probably only wanted to pass a text node. rather edge-casey, but hey...

* added testcase without escaping

* documentation
update as per python3 guidelines to push to pypi

Merge pull request #24 from muellermichel/master

Compatibility with non-JSON objects, html encode feature, better empty object behaviour, cleaned up the code some more
tested for bools and empty nodes

Update jsonconv.py

removed superfluous node cases
new testcases that show off what we now can do with dictlike/listlike objects passed to json2html
non-json object compatibility, making use of duck typing, unicode testing, encode feature
bump version to 1.1.1, support python 3, support dict of list/array of objects
change .md to .rst as pypi doesnt support .md
bump version to 1.1.0, support python 3, support dict of list/array of objects
